    dc:creator "Dózsa-Farkas, Klára; Felföldi, Tamás" ;
    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "The Enchytraeid Fauna (Enchytraeidae, Clitellata) Of The Rax Mountain (Austria) With Description Of Two New Species And Comparison Of Fridericia Discifera Healy, 1975 And F. Alpica Sp. N." ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734609>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734611>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734613> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734609>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Micrograph of Fridericia raxiensis sp. n. A = epidermal glands, B = clitellar glands dorsally (weakly developed), C = brain, D = second nephridium preclitellarly, E–F = coe- lomocytes, G = pharyngeal glands dorsal view (the additional ventral lobes in VII marked with arrows), H = chylus cells in XIV–XV of holotype, I = male copulatory organ (marked with white arrow) and the small subneural gland in XIII (marked with black arrow). (A–B, E in vivo, C–D, F–I fixed, stained; scale bars = 50 Μm)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5734609/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734611>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Micrograph of Fridericia raxiensis sp. n. A–B = sperm funnels (marked with arrows), C = bursal slit (marked with arrow), D–F spermathecae (in E and F the large ectal glands" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5734611/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5734613>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Maximum likelihood (ML) trees of studied Fridericia species based on the ITS region (A), CO1 (B) and H3 genes (C). Bootstrap values greater than 50 are shown at the nodes. Sequences from new species described here appear in bold. A = ML tree of the ITS region" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5734613/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

